At present, fixed operators and their customers are indirectly subsidising mobile operators by paying higher termination rates for calls made from fixed lines to mobiles. This cross-subsidisation
is estimated at €10 billion in Germany for 1998-2006 (
WIK Consult
) and €19 billion in the UK, Germany and France for 1998-2002 (
CERNA-Warwick-WIK
).
